In 3 L (3 quart) saucepan, combine cereal, cornmeal and water. Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring frequently. Reduce heat to medium-low; cook about 8 minutes until very thick, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; stir in corn, Parmesan cheese, seasonings and cilantro. Spread in 33 x 23 cm (13 x 9-inch) baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 180 degrees C (350 degrees F) about 40 minutes or until golden brown. Cool slightly on wire rack. Cut into 12 pieces. Prepare sauce while polenta bakes. In large skillet heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; cook until onion is tender. Stir in beans, tomatoes, corn and salsa. Simmer, uncovered, over medium heat about 15 minutes, or until most of the liquid has been reduced. Stir in cilantro. Place two pieces of warm polenta on plate. Spoon portion of sauce over top and sprinkle with bit of Cheddar cheese.